---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const title = "Insurance for International Buyers | Compare Expat Plans";
const description = "Health insurance guide for Buyers working internationally, covering buying positions abroad, merchandising careers, and global retail and wholesale opportunities.";
const headline = "Insurance for International Buyers";
const subheadline = "Coverage solutions for Buyers working abroad, selecting products internationally, and pursuing careers across retailers, wholesalers, and merchandising organizations worldwide.";
const canonicalPath = "/guides/buyer-insurance";
const heroBackgroundImage = "/images/guides/buyer-insurance-hero.png";

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', label: 'Overview' },
  { id: 'coverage-needs', label: 'Coverage Needs' },
  { id: 'work-settings', label: 'Work Settings' },
  { id: 'credentials', label: 'Credentials' },
  { id: 'occupational-health', label: 'Occupational Health' },
  { id: 'work-demands', label: 'Work Demands' },
  { id: 'career-considerations', label: 'Career Considerations' },
  { id: 'faqs', label: 'FAQs' },
  { id: 'next-steps', label: 'Next Steps' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title={title}
  description={description}
  headline={headline}
  subheadline={subheadline}
  canonicalPath={canonicalPath}
  heroBackgroundImage={heroBackgroundImage}
  tocItems={tocItems}
>
  <article class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">

    <section id="overview">
      <h2>International Buyer Careers</h2>
      <p>
        Buyers select and purchase products for retail or wholesale organizations, analyzing trends, negotiating with vendors, and building assortments that appeal to customers. International buying careers offer opportunities to source globally, attend international trade shows, and develop products with worldwide suppliers.
      </p>
      <p>
        International buying opportunities exist through global retailers sourcing products worldwide, fashion companies with international supply chains, wholesale organizations with global reach, and the increasingly global nature of product sourcing.
      </p>
      <p>
        This guide addresses insurance considerations for Buyers working abroad across retailers, wholesalers, and merchandising organizations worldwide.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="coverage-needs">
      <h2>Coverage Needs for Buyers</h2>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={[
          { key: 'need', header: 'Coverage Need' },
          { key: 'why', header: 'Why It Matters' },
          { key: 'typical', header: 'Coverage Situation?' },
        ]}
        rows={[
          { need: 'General health coverage', why: 'Professional health maintenance', typical: 'Usually employer-provided' },
          { need: 'Mental health support', why: 'Sales targets and trend pressure', typical: 'Often included' },
          { need: 'Travel coverage', why: 'Trade shows and supplier visits', typical: 'Essential for role' },
          { need: 'Ergonomic coverage', why: 'Office-based analysis work', typical: 'Consider for profession' },
          { need: 'Eye coverage', why: 'Product evaluation and screen work', typical: 'Consider including' },
          { need: 'Jet lag support', why: 'International travel demands', typical: 'Consider for travel' },
        ]}
      />

      <h3>Travel Requirements</h3>
      <p>
        Buying often requires significant travel—attending trade shows, visiting suppliers, evaluating products in-person. International buyers travel to fashion weeks, manufacturing regions, and industry events worldwide. Comprehensive travel coverage is essential for the role.
      </p>
      <p>
        The intensity of market weeks and trade shows—multiple cities in rapid succession—creates unique health demands. Coverage supporting recovery from demanding travel schedules helps maintain buying effectiveness.
      </p>

      <h3>Performance Pressure</h3>
      <p>
        Buyers face accountability for sales performance of products they select. Making wrong buying decisions has visible consequences. This performance pressure creates stress benefiting from mental health support.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-settings">
      <h2>Coverage by Work Setting</h2>

      <h3>Fashion Retail</h3>
      <p>
        Fashion buyer. Retail benefits. Trend-driven. Fashion offers creativity.
      </p>

      <h3>Department Store</h3>
      <p>
        Department store buyer. Retail benefits. Category variety. Department stores offer breadth.
      </p>

      <h3>E-commerce</h3>
      <p>
        Online retail buyer. E-commerce benefits. Digital focus. E-commerce offers growth.
      </p>

      <h3>Wholesale</h3>
      <p>
        Wholesale buyer. Wholesaler benefits. Volume focus. Wholesale offers scale.
      </p>

      <h3>Specialty Retail</h3>
      <p>
        Specialty store buyer. Retailer benefits. Category expertise. Specialty offers depth.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Coverage for Buyers"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Buyers working abroad across retailers, wholesalers, and merchandising organizations worldwide."
      buttonText="Compare Buyer Plans"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

    <section id="credentials">
      <h2>Credentials and Professional Recognition</h2>

      <h3>Buying Experience</h3>
      <p>
        Buying track record. Category expertise. Vendor relationships. Experience is primary credential.
      </p>

      <h3>Retail Knowledge</h3>
      <p>
        Retail understanding. Consumer insight. Merchandising expertise. Retail knowledge essential.
      </p>

      <h3>Analytical Skills</h3>
      <p>
        Sales analysis. Trend identification. Performance tracking. Analytical skills drive decisions.
      </p>

      <h3>Fashion/Industry Education</h3>
      <p>
        Merchandising degree. Fashion education. Industry training. Education adds foundation.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="occupational-health">
      <h2>Occupational Health Considerations</h2>

      <h3>Travel Intensity</h3>
      <p>
        Frequent travel. Market weeks. Trade shows. Travel coverage essential.
      </p>

      <h3>Performance Pressure</h3>
      <p>
        Sales accountability. Selection responsibility. Results scrutiny. Mental health support valuable.
      </p>

      <h3>Analysis Work</h3>
      <p>
        Trend research. Sales analysis. Planning work. Ergonomic coverage relevant.
      </p>

      <h3>Seasonal Demands</h3>
      <p>
        Market calendar driven. Seasonal intensity. Deadline pressure. Stress management valuable.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-demands">
      <h2>Managing Work Demands</h2>

      <h3>Assortment Planning</h3>
      <p>
        Product selection. Assortment development. Category planning. Planning defines offering.
      </p>

      <h3>Vendor Management</h3>
      <p>
        Supplier relationships. Negotiation. Product development. Vendors enable assortment.
      </p>

      <h3>Analysis</h3>
      <p>
        Sales tracking. Trend analysis. Performance review. Analysis guides decisions.
      </p>

      <h3>Market Research</h3>
      <p>
        Trend spotting. Competitive analysis. Consumer insight. Research informs buying.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="career-considerations">
      <h2>Career Considerations</h2>

      <h3>Market Cyclicality</h3>
      <p>
        Retail cycles vary. Consumer spending fluctuates. Economic sensitivity. Market affects opportunities.
      </p>

      <h3>Career Paths</h3>
      <p>
        Senior buyer. Divisional merchandise manager. General merchandise manager. Chief merchant. Clear progression.
      </p>

      <h3>Digital Transformation</h3>
      <p>
        Data analytics growing. E-commerce skills valued. Digital merchandising. Technology reshaping role.
      </p>

      <h3>Sustainability Trends</h3>
      <p>
        Sustainable sourcing. Ethical products. Consumer demand shifting. Sustainability increasingly important.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="faqs">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">I'm a buyer considering international work. What should I know?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Travel coverage essential. Employers typically provide benefits. International buying experience valuable.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Do employers provide international coverage?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Major retailers yes. Travel coverage standard for role. Benefits packages typical. Verify specific offer.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Is travel coverage critical?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Yes for buying roles. Trade shows require travel. Market weeks intensive. Travel coverage essential.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Do buying skills transfer internationally?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Core skills yes. Markets differ. Consumer preferences vary. Expertise transfers with learning.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Is mental health coverage important?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Yes for performance pressure. Selection accountability weighs. Results scrutiny stressful. Support valuable.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">What's the career outlook?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Evolving with retail. Digital skills valuable. Analytical focus growing. Outlook variable by segment.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="next-steps">
      <h2>Next Steps</h2>
      <p>
        Start by ensuring comprehensive travel coverage for market weeks and trade shows. Consider mental health coverage for performance pressure. Ensure coverage supports intensive travel schedules. Verify international coverage scope for relocation.
      </p>
      <p>
        Buyers curate products for consumers worldwide. Your coverage should support buying careers—addressing travel demands, covering health maintenance, and protecting you across merchandising work worldwide.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Protect Your Buying Career"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Buyers working abroad across retailers, wholesalers, and merchandising organizations worldwide."
      buttonText="Compare Plans Now"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

  </article>
</PageShell>
